# Cursor rules for aidoc-kit projects
# Copy this file to .cursorrules at the root of your project.

# Always load project architecture before suggesting changes
Always read AGENTS.md and .codemod/ai-knowledge-base.json before suggesting changes to any file.

# Respect the @ai-runtime tag
If a file is tagged @ai-runtime CLIENT UNIQUEMENT, never import server-only modules.
If a file is tagged @ai-runtime SERVER UNIQUEMENT, never import client-only hooks (useState, useEffect, etc.).

# Follow @ai-cascade
When modifying a file, check all files listed under @ai-cascade and verify they are still consistent.

# Run @ai-validate after changes
After any modification, run the command listed under @ai-validate in the modified file's doc block.

# Respect @ai-never
Never violate the rules listed under @ai-never in any file's doc block.
